AmTRAN, Far Eastern, Uni-President: Taiwan Stock Market Preview

-- B y   W e i y i   L i m
-- 
2011-06-24T00:26:51Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-24/amtran-far-eastern-uni-president-taiwan-stock-market-preview.html
Shares of the following companies
may have unusual moves in  Taiwan  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the previous close, unless
stated otherwise.  The Taiex Index fell 53.76, or 0.6 percent, to 8,567.28.  AmTRAN Technology Co. (2489 TT): The maker of Vizio
televisions expects 10 percent of its TVs sold this year to have
three-dimensional display technology, Alpha Wu, Chairman and
Chief Executive Officer said yesterday in Taipei. Shipments of
Internet-connected TVs are expected to pass one million, with
units that combine both Internet and 3D bringing gross margins
30 percent to 50 percent higher than standard TVs, Wu said.
AmTRAN’s full-year goal is to ship 7 million units, Johnny
Huang, a spokesman for the company, said separately. The stock
dropped 0.4 percent to NT$24.50.  Far Eastern Department Stores Co. (2903 TT): The retailer
expects sales to rise from last year’s NT$108.1 billion on
arrivals of individual Chinese tourists, the Economic Daily News
reported, citing company President Hsu Hsueh-Fang. The stock
gained 4.3 percent to NT$56.  Uni-President Enterprises Corp. (1216)  (1216 TT): Taiwan’s largest
food company expects to incur losses of NT$340 million from the
return, disposal, refund and compensation for products
contaminated with plasticizers, the Tainan-based company said in
an exchange filing yesterday. Plasticizers are chemicals used to
soften plastics. The stock lost 0.3 percent to NT$40.  To contact the reporter on this story:
